    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-02-09T22:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-02-09T22:00:00-05:00" n="150"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d150">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">837.61351/3640: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Braden</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-02-09T22:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 9, 1943—10 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 10:13 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>96. For Duggan. My airgrams numbers 254 and 260 of February 6.<note n="77"
                        xml:id="d150fn77">Neither printed.</note> The Prime Minister has just
                    submitted to me a revised and official <pb facs="0174" n="160" xml:id="pg_160"/>
                        memorandum<note n="78" xml:id="d150fn78">This memorandum, partially printed
                            <hi rend="italic">infra</hi>, is the revision of an informal proposal
                        discussed by Prime Minister Zaydín and Ambassador Braden on February 5 and
                        quoted at length in airgram A–254.</note> in the precise form suggested to
                    him last Friday. It submits as a formal counterproposal the provisions set forth
                    in the Department’s telegram No. 127, January 28, 9 p.m. (except relative to
                    molasses offer which is declined, the definite earmarking of 100,000 tons for
                    relief and the segregation, 375 tons for refined sugar and the syrups), the
                    respective paragraphs being followed by parenthetical statements in the form of
                    “Expressions of hope”. The revised memorandum concludes with an annex covering
                        (<hi rend="italic">a</hi>) the Cuban Government’s molasses proposal and (<hi
                        rend="italic">b</hi>) a request that consideration be given to liquidating
                    the 1942 crop by March 15 next.</p>
                <p>[Here follows a description of the additions and modifications that appear in the
                    Prime Minister’s revised memorandum.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Braden</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
